nix profile install: substitute the output for a drvPath-less "fake
derivation" instead of throwing — codebutler/nix-wasm#1.

The guest binary-cache catalog (pkgs.nix, generated by userspace/binary-cache.nix)
lists each package as an attrset that *is* a derivation (type = "derivation")
carrying a `builtins.storePath` `outPath` but deliberately NO `drvPath`: the
NOMMU wasm guest cannot build, so the model is substitute-only — every package
is a prebuilt output pulled from a binary cache, never realised from a deriver.

`nix-env -iA` already installs these via the legacy DrvInfo path (reads
`outPath`, substitutes it, never needs `drvPath`). The new `nix profile install`
CLI went through InstallableAttrPath::toDerivedPaths(), which required a
`drvPath` (to form a `DerivedPath::Built` for realisation) and otherwise threw
`'<name>' is not a derivation`.

Shipping a real `drvPath` is NOT a fix (tested in nix-wasm#1, 6 boots): a
`DerivedPath::Built` is realised by *building* the deriver, which pulls the
native x86_64 build toolchain (xgcc/perl/stdenv) — unbuildable and unrunnable on
the network-less guest — even when the output is already cache-valid; and a
`drvPath` regresses `nix-env -iA` the same way. The two install models are
mutually exclusive on a guest that cannot build.

This is option 1 from the ticket ("treat an already-cache-valid output as
installable without realising the deriver"): when a package has an `outPath` but
no `drvPath`, emit a `DerivedPath::Opaque{outPath}`. An Opaque derived path is
realised purely by substitution (Installable::build2 → buildPathsWithResults
substitutes it from the binary cache and never walks a deriver), so
`nix profile install -f /nix-cache/pkgs.nix <attr>` now substitutes the prebuilt
output exactly like `nix-env -iA`. The element records the output store path with
no flake source (identical to a `nix-env`/`-f` install), so `nix profile
list/remove` work; flake-source upgrade is N/A for a `-f` install, as it already
is for `nix-env`.

Only the drvPath-less branch changes; real derivations (with a `drvPath`) keep
the unchanged `DerivedPath::Built` grouping path, so native/host Nix behaviour is
untouched. `nix-env -iA` lives in src/nix-env/ and is not touched at all.

